"shell now follow HTTP redirections by default (:issue:`2290`); See :command:"
"`fetch` and :command:`shell` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1381
msgid ""
"``HttpErrorMiddleware`` now logs errors with ``INFO`` level instead of "
"``DEBUG``; this is technically **backward incompatible** so please check "
"your log parsers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:1383
msgid ""
"By default, logger names now use a long-form path, e.g. ``[scrapy.extensions."
"logstats]``, instead of the shorter \"top-level\" variant of prior releases "
"(e.g. ``[scrapy]``); this is **backward incompatible** if you have log "
"parsers expecting the short logger name part. You can switch back to short "
"logger names using :setting:`LOG_SHORT_NAMES` set to ``True``."
msgstr ""

